- cs.LM (Lattice Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the expressive limitations of atom-enriched mu-calculi, which can be related to lattice theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with model checking, which is a technique used in programming language verification. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the decidability of model checking on orbit-finite structures, which can be related to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the expressive power of atom-enriched mu-calculi, which can be related to formal languages and automata theory.
